        <h1>Documentation: Simple Authentication App</h1>
        <p>This is a simple authentication app built using Node.js, TypeScript, Express, MongoDB, and Handlebars for the front end. It follows the MVC (Model-View-Controller) architecture.</p>
        
        <h2>Features</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>User Registration with bcryptjs password hashing.</li>
            <li>Session-based authentication with express-session.</li>
            <li>Error handling for duplicate usernames and server issues.</li>
            <li>Dockerized MongoDB for consistency.</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2>Technologies Used</h2>
        <h3>Backend:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Node.js, Express, TypeScript, MongoDB (Mongoose)</li>
            <li>bcryptjs, express-session</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3>Frontend:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Handlebars, Bootstrap</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2>Setup & Run</h2>
        <h3>1. Prerequisites</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Node.js (v16+), Docker (optional)</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3>2. Clone & Install</h3>
        <pre><code>git clone &lt;repository-url&gt;
cd auth-app
npm install</code></pre>
        
        <h3>3. Configure Environment</h3>
        <pre><code>SESSION_SECRET=your-secret-key
MONGO_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/auth_app</code></pre>
        
        <h3>4. Run the App</h3>
        <p>Development Mode:</p>
        <pre><code>npm run dev</code></pre>
        <p>Production Mode:</p>
        <pre><code>npm run build
npm start</code></pre>
        <p>Access at: <code>http://localhost:3000</code>.</p>
        
